definition: ahead of schedule/sooner than planned/to bring forward (to an earlier time)
to carry (hanging down from the hand)/to lift/to put forward/to mention/to raise (an issue)/upwards character stroke/lifting brush stroke (in painting)/scoop for measuring liquid

sentences.english: Tens of thousands of flag-waving activists called for early elections.
sentences.chinese: 數以萬計揮舞着國旗的積極分子要求提早進行選舉。

sentences.english: If the ball arrives one second beforehand, will you yield it to the wind?
sentences.chinese: 如果球兒提早了一秒飛來，你是否聽任它消逝在風中？

sentences.english: Some of those launches are expected to take place as early as this weekend.
sentences.chinese: 這是預定好的計畫只是提早到這星期實行。

sentences.english: Girdling and other treatments can induce polypoid plants to flower earlier.
sentences.chinese: 用環剝樹皮等方法可以誘導多倍體無性系提早開花。

sentences.english: Of course you may hope to sell long before then.
sentences.chinese: 當然你或許不會等那麼久，提早出手拋售黃金。

sentences.english: Can I skip to this course?
sentences.chinese: 我能否提早插班讀這門課程？

sentences.english: Early retirement also seemed kinder than mass lay-offs.
sentences.chinese: 提早退休似乎比大範圍的失業更加仁慈。

sentences.english: The game was brought to a premature end by heavy rain.
sentences.chinese: 這場比賽因爲雨勢太大而提早結束。

sentences.english: Had the board brought in a new face too early, it might have attracted mud.
sentences.chinese: 倘若董事會提早推出一張新面孔，可能會招致非議。

sentences.english: The longer treated time was, the weaker plants were. (4) Garlic could bolt earlier with low temperature treatment.
sentences.chinese: 播前低溫處理可提早大蒜的抽薹期。

sentences.english: He got off early and went to the clinic.
sentences.chinese: 他提早下班，到門診所看病去了。

sentences.english: Perhaps the MKI MLU will start earlier as well.
sentences.chinese: 此外，也許MKI會提早開始中期延壽升級。

sentences.english: Meanwhile, resection of Eyestalk can also promote pre- spawning.
sentences.chinese: 同時，切除眼柄，也能促進克氏原螯蝦提早產卵。

sentences.english: The warm weather unfroze the ground early.
sentences.chinese: 暖和的天氣使大地提早解凍。

sentences.english: Black can improve the heat-absorbing capability and speed up the spring planting.
sentences.chinese: 黑色有助吸熱及提早春天種植。

definition: to shift to an earlier date/to do sth ahead of time/in advance
at the earliest possible time/as soon as possible
to delay/to postpone/to keep putting sth off/to procrastinate/(computing) to lag
to push back (progress, the times etc)
to wait until/by the time when (sth is ready etc)
